  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This method can efficiently aggregate nodes of the same type based on their features and the whole graph topology information.",
    "For the more complex structure of hypergraph, Hyperedge pooling (Zhang et al. 2021c) introduces personalized PageRank (PPR) (Haveliwala 2003) values as the key basis for pooling.",
    "This approach fully utilizes the feature information of nodes as well as the local and global structural properties of the hypergraph.",
    "It achieves effective coarsening of the hypergraph by adaptively selecting and retaining a subset of important hyperedges.",
    "This process not only reduces the amount of computation but also preserves the key structural information of the hypergraph, enabling tasks such as subgraph matching to be accomplished more quickly and accurately."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
